[ a                      owl:Axiom ;
  rdfs:comment           "Evidence statement (PMID:8305738): As shown in Figure 2, the Sem-5 fusion protein could associate with the hEGFR in EGF-stimulated cells but not in nonstimulated cells. GST alone shows no binding to the hEGFR. Thus, Sem-5 is capable of binding to EGFstimulated hEGFR. " , "Annotation comment: As of 2023-10-13, there is no evidence for a direct physical interaction between LET-23 and SEM-5." ;
  dc:contributor         "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196" ;
